## Key Decisions

### Workspace Structure
- Root folders: `brand/`, `website/`, `documents/`, `ops/`
- Numbered prefixes avoided — descriptive folder names are clearer
- Each folder has a README so any team member can navigate without asking

### Website Architecture
- Next.js 15, App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v3
- Framer Motion 11 for animations
- Modular: each page section is a standalone module in `website/modules/`
- `"use client"` only where needed (hero for motion, nav for state)
- Build verified clean: static prerender, 0 errors

### Workspace Restructure (2026-04-14)
- Previously, the Next.js code lived at repo root (`app/`, `modules/`, etc.) with a separate Next 16 WIP scaffold in `website/`.
- Restructured: moved the live Next 15 code into `website/` (via `git mv`, history preserved).
- Discarded the Next 16 WIP scaffold.
- Result: `website/` is fully self-contained and portable. Repo root only holds `brand/`, `documents/`, `ops/`, `website/`, and workspace docs.
- `ops/deployment.md` updated: VPS deploy now does `cd website && npm install && npm run build` before `pm2 restart`.
- VPS migration required before next deploy — see deployment.md for one-time steps.

### Documents
- All documents in Markdown — portable, no tool dependency
- Invoice numbering convention: SH-YYYY-NNN (e.g. SH-2026-001)
- Company profile covers: who we are, what we do, TaoLink, Landlord HQ

